problem:
Jia and Yi are solving the system of equations simultaneously:
$$
\begin{cases}
& ax+by=2, \\
& cx-3y=-2.
\end{cases}
$$
Jia correctly solves to get
$$
\begin{cases}
& x=1, \\
& y=-1;
\end{cases}
$$
Yi, due to copying the value of $c$ incorrectly, gets the wrong solution
$$
\begin{cases}
& x=2, \\
& y=-6.
\end{cases}
$$
Find the values of $a$, $b$, and $c$.
